real_mean = seq(1, 10, 1)*100
samples = 40
exposure = round(rnorm(samples, 10000, 100))
multinomial_pure = function(){
    
    model_simple = "
    data{
    int T;
    int G;
    int y[T, G];
    int exposure[T];
    }
    parameters{
    vector[G] mu;
    }
    transformed parameters{
        vector[G] mu_softmax = softmax(mu);
    }
    model{
    sum(mu) ~ normal(0, 0.001 * G);
    for(t in 1:T) y[t] ~ multinomial( mu_softmax );
    }
    generated quantities{
    int y_gen[T, G];
    for(t in 1:T) y_gen[t] = multinomial_rng( mu_softmax, exposure[t] );
    
    }
    
    "
    fit = stan(
        model_code = model_simple,
        data = list(
            T = samples,
            G = length(real_mean),
            y = y,
            exposure = exposure
        ),
        cores = 4,
        iter = 800
    )
    
    list(
        fit = fit,
        getn = fit %>%
            gather_samples(y_gen[sample_idx, gene_idx] ) %>%
            mean_qi() 
    )
    
}

multinomial_overdispersed= function(){
    
    model_simple = "
        data{
        int T;
        int G;
        int y[T, G];
    int exposure[T];

        }
        parameters{
        vector[G] alpha_z[T];
        vector[G] mu;
        real sigma;
        }
        transformed parameters{
        vector[G] mu_softmax = softmax(mu);
        
        vector[G] alpha[T];
        real<lower=0> exp_sigma = exp(sigma);
        
        for(t in 1:T) alpha[t] = mu + alpha_z[t] * exp_sigma;
        }
        model{
        
        for(t in 1:T) alpha_z[t] ~ normal(0, 1);
        
        sum(mu) ~ normal(0, 0.001 * G);
        for(t in 1:T) y[t] ~ multinomial( softmax( alpha[t] ) );
        
        sigma ~ cauchy(0, 2.5);
        }
        generated quantities{
        int y_gen[T, G];
        vector[G] mu_od;
        for(g in 1:G) mu_od[g] = normal_rng( mu[g] , exp_sigma );
        for(t in 1:T) y_gen[t] = multinomial_rng( softmax( mu_od ), exposure[t] );
        
        }
    
    "
    
    fit = stan(
        model_code = model_simple,
        data = list(
            T = samples,
            G = length(real_mean),
            y = y,
            exposure = exposure
        ),
        cores = 4,
        iter = 800
    )
    
    list(
        fit = fit,
        getn = fit %>%
            gather_samples(y_gen[sample_idx, gene_idx] ) %>%
            mean_qi() 
    )
    
}

multinomial_overdispersed_2= function(){
    
    model_simple = "
        data{
        int T;
        int G;
        int y[T, G];
    int exposure[T];

        }
        parameters{
        vector[G] alpha_z;
        vector[G] mu;
        real sigma;
        }
        transformed parameters{
        vector[G] mu_softmax = softmax(mu);
        real<lower=0> exp_sigma = exp(sigma);

        vector[G] alpha = mu + alpha_z * exp_sigma;
        }
        model{
        
        alpha_z ~ normal(0, 1);
        
        sum(mu) ~ normal(0, 0.001 * G);
        for(t in 1:T) y[t] ~ multinomial( softmax( alpha ) );
        
        sigma ~ normal(0, 5);
        }
        generated quantities{
        int y_gen[T, G];
        vector[G] mu_od;
        for(g in 1:G) mu_od[g] = normal_rng( mu[g] , exp_sigma );
        for(t in 1:T) y_gen[t] = multinomial_rng( softmax( mu_od ), exposure[t] );
        
        }
    
    "
    
    fit = stan(
        model_code = model_simple,
        data = list(
            T = samples,
            G = length(real_mean),
            y = y,
            exposure = exposure
        ),
        cores = 4,
        iter = 800
    )
    
    list(
        fit = fit,
        getn = fit %>%
            gather_samples(y_gen[sample_idx, gene_idx] ) %>%
            mean_qi() 
    )
    
}

multinomial_over_overdispersed= function(){
    
    model_simple = "
    data{
    int T;
    int G;
    int y[T, G];
    int exposure[T];

    }
    parameters{
    vector[G] alpha_z[T];
    vector[G] mu;
    real sigma;
    real sigma_slope;

    }
    transformed parameters{
    vector[G] mu_softmax = softmax(mu);
    vector[G] alpha[T];

    for(t in 1:T) alpha[t] = mu + alpha_z[t] .* exp( sigma + mu * sigma_slope) ;
    
    }
    model{
    
    for(t in 1:T) alpha_z[t] ~ normal(0, 1);
    
    sum(mu) ~ normal(0, 0.001 * G);
    for(t in 1:T) y[t] ~ multinomial( softmax( alpha[t] ) );
    
    sigma ~ cauchy(0, 2.5);
    sigma_slope ~ normal(0,5);
    }
    generated quantities{
    int y_gen[T, G];

    for(t in 1:T) y_gen[t] = multinomial_rng( softmax( alpha[t] ), exposure[t] );
    
    }
    
    "
    
    fit = stan(
        model_code = model_simple,
        data = list(
            T = samples,
            G = length(real_mean),
            y = y,
            exposure = exposure
        ),
        cores = 4,
        iter = 800
    )
    
    list(
        fit = fit,
        getn = fit %>%
            gather_samples(y_gen[sample_idx, gene_idx] ) %>%
            mean_qi() 
    )
    
}

negative_binomial= function(){
    
    model_simple = "
    data{
    int T;
    int G;
    int y[T, G];

    }
    parameters{
    vector[G] alpha_z[T];
    vector[G] mu;
    real<lower=0> sigma;
    vector[T] exposure;

    }
    transformed parameters{
    vector[G] mu_softmax = softmax(mu);
    }
    model{
    
    for(t in 1:T) alpha_z[t] ~ normal(0, 1);
    for(t in 1:T) y[t] ~ neg_binomial_2_log( exposure[t] + mu, sigma );
    
    sigma ~ cauchy(0, 2.5);
    exposure ~ cauchy(0, 2.5);
    }
    generated quantities{
    int y_gen[T, G];

    for(t in 1:T) for(g in 1:G) y_gen[t,g] = neg_binomial_2_log_rng( exposure[t] + mu[g], sigma);
    
    }
    
    "
    
    fit = stan(
        model_code = model_simple,
        data = list(
            T = samples,
            G = length(real_mean),
            y = y
        ),
        cores = 4,
        iter = 800
    )
    
    list(
        fit = fit,
        getn = fit %>%
            gather_samples(y_gen[sample_idx, gene_idx] ) %>%
            mean_qi() 
    )
    
}

plot_gen = function(x){
    
        my_noise = rnorm( x %>% nrow(), 0, 0.1  )

        
    x %>%
        
        # Add gene names
        left_join(
            tibble(
                gene_idx = 1:ncol(y),
                gene =     colnames(y)
            ),
            by = "gene_idx"
        ) %>%
        
        # Attach observed y
        left_join(
            y %>% 
                mutate(sample_idx = 1:!!samples) %>% 
                gather(gene_idx, observed, -sample_idx) %>% 
                mutate(gene_idx = as.integer(gene_idx)),
            by = c("sample_idx", "gene_idx")
        ) %>%
        
        # Plot
        ggplot(aes(x=gene_idx+my_noise, y=observed, group=interaction(gene_idx, sample_idx))) +
        geom_point(color="red") +
        geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=conf.low, ymax=conf.high), width = 0, alpha=0.2) +
        theme_bw()
    
}

plot_mu = function(x){
    
    x %>%
        # Get samples
        gather_samples(mu_softmax[gene_idx] ) %>%
        mean_qi() %>%
        ungroup() %>%
    
        # Add gene names
        left_join(
            tibble(
                gene_idx = 1:ncol(y),
                gene =     colnames(y)
            ),
            by = "gene_idx"
        ) %>%
        
        # Attach real y
            left_join(
                tibble(
                    gene_idx = 1:length(!!real_mean),
                    real =     !!real_mean
                ),
                by = "gene_idx"
            ) %>%
            
        # softmax real y
        mutate(real = real/sum(real)) %>%
        
        # Plot
        ggplot(aes(x=gene_idx, y=real, group=interaction(gene_idx))) +
        geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=conf.low, ymax=conf.high), width = 0) +
        geom_point(color="red") +
        geom_point(aes(x=gene_idx, y=real), color="green") +
        theme_bw()
    
}

plot_inference = function(plist, title){
    
    n <- length(plist)
    nCol <- floor(sqrt(n))
    do.call("grid.arrange", c(plist, ncol=nCol))
    
}
